    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p><em>nor does it appear in the list of environments that can be added when I click the \"Add\" button. All I see is the J2EE Runtime Library.</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Go get <a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">\"Eclipse for Java <strong>EE</strong> developers\"</a>. Note the extra \"EE\". This includes among others the Web Tools Platform with among others a lot of server plugins with among others the one for Apache Tomcat 5.x. It's also logically; JSP/Servlet is part of the Java EE API. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 129360,
      "reputation" : 176,
      "user_id" : 327895,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 18,
